## Rules
1. Create exactly 3-5 connected databases that work together as a system
2. Use relations to link related databases (e.g., Client CRM → Invoice Tracker)
3. Each database must have 5-8 realistic sample entries with meaningful data
4. Include at least one board view, one calendar view, and one table view across all databases
5. Properties must include a mix of: title, select, date, number, email, url, checkbox, status, relation, rollup, formula, rich_text, phone, multi_select, files
6. Use the market research context to make the databases feel tailored to the specific niche — property names, options, and sample data should reflect real client types, pricing tiers, and workflows relevant to {{ niche }}
7. IMPORTANT: No content storage databases. No "Guide Repository", "SOP Archive", "Template Library", or similar pages — those belong in the ZIP deliverable, not in Notion

